德克萨斯州州长[[格雷格·阿博特|格雷格·阿博特]]命令{{le|德克萨斯州公共安全部|Texas Department of Public Safety}}向达拉斯提供一切请求的协助。他还在案发后表示：“在这种时候，我们必须记住并强调团结美国人的重要性<ref name=KXAN.Shot>{{cite web|url=http://kxan.com/2016/07/07/two-police-officers-shot-during-protests-in-dallas/|title=Five police officers shot dead in downtown Dallas shooting|publisher=KXAN|date=2016-07-07|accessdate=2016-07-07|first=Andy|last=Jechow|archive-date=2017-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927024605/http://kxan.com/2016/07/07/two-police-officers-shot-during-protests-in-dallas/|dead-url=no}}</ref>”。州长助理{{le|丹·帕特里克 (政治人物)|Dan Patrick (politician)|丹·帕特里克}}将暴力事件归因于社交媒体上的个人、“此前的黑人民權運動示威者”，还有其他持有反警方观点的人士<ref name=Fox.Patrick>{{cite web|url=http://video.foxnews.com/v/5027952148001/texas-lt-gov-patrick-on-dallas-ambush-this-has-to-end/?#sp=show-clips|title=Texas Lt. Gov. Patrick on Dallas ambush: 'This has to end'|publisher=Fox News|date=2016-07-08|accessdate=2016-07-09|archive-date=2016-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160711125950/http://video.foxnews.com/v/5027952148001/texas-lt-gov-patrick-on-dallas-ambush-this-has-to-end#sp=show-clips|dead-url=no}}</ref>，后来他为他的发言道歉<ref name=CNN.Patrick>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/08/politics/dan-patrick-black-lives-matter-dallas/|title=Texas official walks back remark calling Dallas protesters 'hypocrites'|publisher=CNN|date=2016-07-08|accessdate=2016-07-09|first=Eugene|last=Scott|archive-date=2016-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709081737/http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/08/politics/dan-patrick-black-lives-matter-dallas/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[美国总统|总统]][[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]称枪击案是一场“恶毒、有预谋的卑鄙袭击”，是一场“惨重的悲剧”<ref name=ABC.Obama>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/president-obama-receiving-regular-updates-dallas-shooting/story?id=40425624|title=President Obama Describes Dallas Shootings As 'Vicious, Calculated, Despicable Attack'|publisher=ABC News|date=2016-07-08|accessdate=2016-07-08|first1=Alexander|last1=Mallin|first2=David|last2=Caplan|archive-date=2016-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708085210/http://abcnews.go.com/US/president-obama-receiving-regular-updates-dallas-shooting/story?id=40425624|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他还不忘呼吁[[枪支管制|控枪]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Blake|first1=Aaron|title=Why President Obama went right to gun control after five police officers were killed in Dallas|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/07/08/why-president-obama-went-right-to-gun-control-after-five-police-were-killed-in-dallas/|accessdate=2016-07-08|work=The Washington Post|date=2016-07-08|archive-date=2016-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709020738/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/07/08/why-president-obama-went-right-to-gun-control-after-five-police-were-killed-in-dallas/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。{{le|美国警察同业会|Fraternal Order of Police}}称据调查枪击案是一次[[仇恨犯罪|仇恨犯罪]]<ref name=nypost /><ref name=yahoonews>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/police-union-criticizes-obama-shooting-response-calls-for-hate-crime-investigation-154938936.html|title=Police union criticizes Obama shooting response, calls for hate crime investigation|publisher=Yahoo! News|date=2016-07-08|accessdate=2016-07-08|first1=Liz|last1=Goodwin|archive-date=2016-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709230550/https://www.yahoo.com/news/police-union-criticizes-obama-shooting-response-calls-for-hate-crime-investigation-154938936.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | publisher=Fraternal Order of Police | title=FOP: Justice Needs to Investigate Dallas Shootings as a Hate Crime | date=2016-07-08 | access-date=2016-07-08 | url=https://fop.net/CmsDocument/Doc/pr_2016-0708.pdf | archive-date=2016-08-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160813090703/https://fop.net/CmsDocument/Doc/pr_2016-0708.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>，并批评总统奥巴马的回应，表示他需要向每个人演讲，而非仅向警方或非裔美国人演讲<ref name=yahoonews/>。

“黑人的命也是命”运动领导人谴责了枪击事件<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-36752603|title=Dallas shooting suspect Micah Johnson 'acted alone'|work=BBC News|date=2016-07-09|accessdate=2016-07-09|archive-date=2016-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708225218/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-36752603|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[美国全国步枪协会|美国全国步枪协会]]表示“深切悲痛”，并表达了“最深切的哀悼”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/dallas-massacre-nra-sends-selective-condolences-article-1.2704517|title=NRA sends condolences to Dallas victims' families, snubs Castile and Sterling’s relatives|first=Reuven|last=Blau|work=The New York Daily News|date=2016-07-08|accessdate=2016-07-09|archive-date=2016-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160709141617/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/dallas-massacre-nra-sends-selective-condolences-article-1.2704517|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[共和党_(美国)|共和党]]总统候选人[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]表示：“我们必须恢复法律与秩序。我们必须恢复人民对在他们家中和走在街上时感到安全的信心。路易斯安那和明尼苏达州两名市民的悲剧死亡是毫无意义的，这提醒我们还有多少工作需要做<ref name=guardian20160708/>。”他补充道，枪击事件是“针对我们国家的一场袭击”，并表示“每一个美国人都有在安稳祥和环境中生活的权利”<ref name=nyt20160709/>。[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]总统候选人[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]则表示：“我对履行神圣指责保护和平示威者的警察、他们的家人和同事表示哀悼和慰问<ref name=guardian20160708>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2016/jul/08/dallas-shooting-tragedies|title='All of these tragedies'|first=Tom|last=McCarthy|work=The Guardian|date=2016-07-08|accessdate=2016-07-09|archive-date=2016-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708231203/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2016/jul/08/dallas-shooting-tragedies|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”她表示，有鉴于非裔美国人社区警方的关系紧张，白种美国人“不得不聆听我们的非洲裔同胞发出的合理哭诉”<ref name=nyt20160709>{{cite news | last=Chozick | first=Amy | title=Hillary Clinton and Donald Trump Strike Different Tones After Dallas Shooting | work=The New York Times | date=2016-07-08 | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/09/us/politics/clinton-trump-shooting-reaction.html | accessdate=2016-07-09 | archive-date=2016-07-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708183430/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/09/us/politics/clinton-trump-shooting-reaction.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

